CatDescriptText: There is a sign with photo collage on back wall reading "The J. R. Watkins Co., branches under race management - Oldest, established 1868 - Largest, 15,000 dealers.  The images are of the Pittsburgh, Baltimore, Chicago, Harlem, and Philadelphia branches with their respective managers.  Another sign on desk reads "The open door to success, is it open for you?"
TitMainTitle: Three men and a woman gathered around a desk in office or booth for The J.R.Watkins Company
